# REQUIRED. Prisma schema uses provider = postgresql (see prisma/schema.prisma).
#
# Local: copy to .env (never commit .env). Use Docker Postgres, Neon dev branch, or similar:
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@localhost:5432/seo_geo"
#
# Vercel: connect Vercel Postgres (Storage) to the project — it usually sets DATABASE_URL and/or
# POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL. lib/db.ts maps POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL → DATABASE_URL when needed.
# After the first connect, from a machine with DB access run:
#   npx prisma db push
# (or pull env with `vercel env pull` then db push) so tables exist before the app serves traffic.

# Optional — token → siteId map for /report/<token> and /portal/<token>
# CLIENT_REPORT_TOKENS_JSON='{"your-secret-token":"clxxxxxxxxsiteid"}'

# Optional — report layout brand (server-only)
# CLIENT_REPORT_BRAND_NAME="Your agency name"

# Optional — client portal product shell (browser-safe)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_PRODUCT_NAME="Program portal"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_OFFERING_TAGLINE="Status, reports, and next steps."
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_SUPPORT_CONTACT="Email or link for support."
